1
00:01:33,193 --> 00:01:33,960
We'll fly that way.

2
00:01:35,228 --> 00:01:36,162
Beyond the mountains.

3
00:01:36,696 --> 00:01:37,530
Beyond the sea.

4
00:02:01,154 --> 00:02:01,588
Look.

5
00:02:02,455 --> 00:02:03,690
The sky's about to brighten.

6
00:02:05,158 --> 00:02:07,093
The sun rises every day.

7
00:02:08,428 --> 00:02:09,762
Another brand-new day.

8
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:15,735
Another brand-new day.

9
00:02:25,712 --> 00:02:26,446
Did you catch a chill?

10
00:02:26,479 --> 00:02:26,946
No.

11
00:02:27,947 --> 00:02:29,549
Someone must be thinking about me.

12
00:02:29,849 --> 00:02:30,283
Wait.

13
00:02:31,951 --> 00:02:33,786
Maybe Brother Xu is cursing me.

14
00:02:35,188 --> 00:02:35,955
He wouldn't dare.

15
00:02:40,126 --> 00:02:40,593
Come on.

16
00:02:41,161 --> 00:02:41,895
Let's go back.

17
00:02:43,663 --> 00:02:44,631
I'm cold.

18
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:47,767
Let's go.

19
00:02:49,068 --> 00:02:49,769
It really is a little cold.

20
00:02:50,770 --> 00:02:51,404
Wait here.

21
00:03:02,882 --> 00:03:03,249
Let's go.

22
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:33,079
What's that?

23
00:03:36,849 --> 00:03:38,384
For the cleaner.

24
00:03:51,831 --> 00:03:52,966
Thank God.

25
00:04:07,013 --> 00:04:07,847
Boss, you wanted me?

26
00:04:09,449 --> 00:04:10,583
Come on. Sit, sit.

27
00:04:10,850 --> 00:04:11,684
Right away. Right away.

28
00:04:12,051 --> 00:04:12,752
What is it?

29
00:04:13,553 --> 00:04:14,554
What's up?

30
00:04:15,054 --> 00:04:15,989
Sit. Sit down.

31
00:04:21,928 --> 00:04:22,962
Take a look.

32
00:04:23,663 --> 00:04:24,597
the distribution authorization

33
00:04:24,597 --> 00:04:26,165
for the fourth-generation vascular plug

34
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:28,735
Piece of cake.

35
00:04:28,935 --> 00:04:29,736
That's my girl.

36
00:04:32,372 --> 00:04:33,406
I haven't finished reading.

37
00:04:37,243 --> 00:04:39,145
I just can't get Zhou Xiaofeng

38
00:04:39,212 --> 00:04:40,113
to come out for dinner.

39
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,748
Yet he's still helping us this much.

40
00:04:42,482 --> 00:04:43,383
Here's what I'm thinking.

41
00:04:44,517 --> 00:04:46,286
Why don't you request a budget

42
00:04:46,586 --> 00:04:47,854
and get him a gift?

43
00:04:48,254 --> 00:04:49,088
We really don't need to.

44
00:04:49,255 --> 00:04:50,189
He's doing this procedure

45
00:04:50,290 --> 00:04:51,557
for the patient, not for a gift.

46
00:04:52,492 --> 00:04:53,192
Still,

47
00:04:54,527 --> 00:04:55,528
no matter how you look at it,

48
00:04:55,928 --> 00:04:56,729
he's brought us

49
00:04:56,729 --> 00:04:57,730
a lot of business.

50
00:04:58,064 --> 00:04:59,732
If we say nothing at all,

51
00:04:59,999 --> 00:05:01,434
won't that look ungrateful?

52
00:05:02,268 --> 00:05:03,302
With him,

53
00:05:04,203 --> 00:05:05,905
everything comes down to one thing:

54
00:05:06,272 --> 00:05:07,840
what's best for the patient.

55
00:05:08,508 --> 00:05:09,709
As long as it helps the patient,

56
00:05:10,243 --> 00:05:11,911
we just need a good product

57
00:05:12,011 --> 00:05:12,612
and solid technical support.

58
00:05:12,645 --> 00:05:13,613
That's how we win him over.

59
00:05:13,846 --> 00:05:15,081
Forget everything else.

60
00:05:15,715 --> 00:05:16,916
I know him pretty well.

61
00:05:17,483 --> 00:05:18,785
Don't try any of your shady tricks

62
00:05:18,885 --> 00:05:20,153
on him.

63
00:05:20,953 --> 00:05:22,388
You'll only outsmart yourself

64
00:05:23,189 --> 00:05:24,023
and make things worse.

65
00:05:24,590 --> 00:05:24,924
All right.

66
00:05:25,491 --> 00:05:26,092
I'll listen to you.

67
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:27,760
Right.

68
00:05:28,394 --> 00:05:29,195
And don't neglect Cardiac Surgery

69
00:05:29,729 --> 00:05:31,030
in favor of Cardiology.

70
00:05:32,665 --> 00:05:33,966
That Sheng Nian

71
00:05:34,033 --> 00:05:35,735
isn't easy to deal with.

72
00:05:39,105 --> 00:05:40,406
I know. I've got it handled.

73
00:05:52,952 --> 00:05:53,653
Director Sheng.

74
00:05:55,054 --> 00:05:56,389
Today marks your hundredth

75
00:05:56,422 --> 00:05:57,523
off-pump coronary bypass

76
00:05:57,523 --> 00:05:58,925
since joining Dongli Hospital.

77
00:05:58,958 --> 00:06:00,026
To celebrate,

78
00:06:00,093 --> 00:06:01,494
I prepared a cake and flowers

79
00:06:01,794 --> 00:06:02,362
and asked Dr. Liu

80
00:06:02,362 --> 00:06:03,362
to put them in your office.

81
00:06:04,997 --> 00:06:06,132
What's there to celebrate?

82
00:06:06,766 --> 00:06:07,667
There aren't many experts

83
00:06:07,667 --> 00:06:09,035
in the field with your achievements.

84
00:06:09,168 --> 00:06:10,503
You're a role model for your peers.

85
00:06:11,771 --> 00:06:12,372
Manager Ouyang,

86
00:06:12,905 --> 00:06:13,306
you shouldn't have.

87
00:06:13,673 --> 00:06:14,407
It's the least I could do.

88
00:06:14,974 --> 00:06:16,075
You and Director Zhou

89
00:06:16,109 --> 00:06:16,943
really made a splash

90
00:06:17,310 --> 00:06:18,344
with that rural free clinic.

91
00:06:19,479 --> 00:06:21,047
I was only helping the directors

92
00:06:21,147 --> 00:06:22,482
with errands and logistics.

93
00:06:23,249 --> 00:06:25,051
Now that you've built that camaraderie,

94
00:06:25,284 --> 00:06:26,519
Director Zhou

95
00:06:26,652 --> 00:06:27,954
give you more support professionally

96
00:06:28,287 --> 00:06:30,289
At least he won't suddenly ask

97
00:06:30,523 --> 00:06:31,591
for someone else,

98
00:06:31,724 --> 00:06:32,358
and I won't need to use my connections

99
00:06:32,992 --> 00:06:34,494
to plead your case.

100
00:06:34,494 --> 00:06:35,628
Director Sheng, I'll always remember

101
00:06:36,162 --> 00:06:37,130
how much you've helped me.

102
00:06:37,196 --> 00:06:39,065
So your needs,

103
00:06:39,332 --> 00:06:40,333
and everything Cardiac Surgery needs,

104
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:40,933
will always come first.

105
00:06:42,368 --> 00:06:42,935
Also,

106
00:06:43,302 --> 00:06:44,971
at the European Cardiology Summit,

107
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:46,038
one of our manufacturers

108
00:06:46,105 --> 00:06:47,440
is sponsoring a themed session.

109
00:06:47,607 --> 00:06:48,708
They've asked our company

110
00:06:48,808 --> 00:06:50,276
to invite a major expert

111
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:51,411
as a guest speaker.

112
00:06:51,677 --> 00:06:52,478
I was wondering whether

113
00:06:52,512 --> 00:06:53,613
you'd have the time and interest.

114
00:06:54,046 --> 00:06:54,947
Is it a domestic brand?

115
00:06:55,281 --> 00:06:55,548
Yes.

116
00:06:55,948 --> 00:06:57,984
That's why they want

117
00:06:58,251 --> 00:06:59,152
a leading domestic expert

118
00:06:59,285 --> 00:07:00,319
to give the presentation.

119
00:07:01,988 --> 00:07:04,791
If my schedule allows,

120
00:07:04,791 --> 00:07:05,425
I can consider it.

121
00:07:06,125 --> 00:07:07,293
Why are invitations going out

122
00:07:07,427 --> 00:07:08,194
so early this year?

123
00:07:08,427 --> 00:07:09,128
Normally,

124
00:07:09,128 --> 00:07:09,962
they wouldn't be this early.

125
00:07:10,163 --> 00:07:11,531
But it's our own client

126
00:07:11,564 --> 00:07:12,131
sponsoring the session.

127
00:07:12,331 --> 00:07:13,466
I've kept it in mind

128
00:07:13,633 --> 00:07:14,467
and asked about it every day.

129
00:07:15,001 --> 00:07:15,635
There's only one slot.

130
00:07:17,036 --> 00:07:18,004
Cost reduction and efficiency, right?

131
00:07:18,437 --> 00:07:18,805
Boss,

132
00:07:20,006 --> 00:07:21,974
can I get a few more slots

133
00:07:22,275 --> 00:07:23,409
for the European Cardiology Summit this year?

134
00:07:24,010 --> 00:07:24,510
No problem.

135
00:07:25,311 --> 00:07:25,878
I'll give you two.

136
00:07:26,412 --> 00:07:27,246
This one slot

137
00:07:27,313 --> 00:07:28,281
was already hard-won.

138
00:07:28,648 --> 00:07:29,215
Other companies

139
00:07:29,248 --> 00:07:30,516
may not get even one.

140
00:07:31,551 --> 00:07:32,585
Isn't Cardiology going?

141
00:07:33,085 --> 00:07:34,187
I'm prioritizing your side.

142
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:35,655
Once you're confirmed,

143
00:07:35,955 --> 00:07:37,123
I'll try to get one more.

144
00:07:37,690 --> 00:07:39,091
If I can't,

145
00:07:39,192 --> 00:07:40,293
there's nothing more I can do.

146
00:07:48,868 --> 00:07:49,502
Quan,

147
00:07:49,669 --> 00:07:51,704
why is my heart pounding?

148
00:07:52,305 --> 00:07:53,439
If it stopped, you'd be dead.

149
00:07:54,841 --> 00:07:55,274
All right, all right.

150
00:07:55,608 --> 00:07:56,108
Seriously.

151
00:07:57,877 --> 00:07:58,344
What are you saying?

152
00:07:58,344 --> 00:07:59,045
Zhang Diao'e,

153
00:07:59,545 --> 00:08:00,079
you can go sign

154
00:08:00,079 --> 00:08:01,214
the surgical consent form.

155
00:08:01,547 --> 00:08:01,814
Well...

156
00:08:02,348 --> 00:08:03,082
I'll go right away.

157
00:08:05,117 --> 00:08:05,585
Oh no.

158
00:08:06,552 --> 00:08:08,054
It's only a minor procedure under local anesthesia.

159
00:08:08,087 --> 00:08:08,688
Don't be nervous.

160
00:08:09,121 --> 00:08:10,523
Here, I've mixed your medicine.

161
00:08:11,023 --> 00:08:11,691
It's a little hot.

162
00:08:12,425 --> 00:08:13,159
Drink it when you get back.

163
00:08:13,559 --> 00:08:14,827
Let me finish it first.

164
00:08:14,927 --> 00:08:15,895
I need some courage.

165
00:08:16,095 --> 00:08:17,063
Go sign the consent first.

166
00:08:17,263 --> 00:08:18,965
I'm really scared.

167
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:21,734
I'm going.

168
00:08:25,371 --> 00:08:26,372
You understood

169
00:08:26,439 --> 00:08:27,440
everything I just explained, right?

170
00:08:27,907 --> 00:08:29,642
Yes, pretty doctor.

171
00:08:30,176 --> 00:08:32,211
There are just so many words.

172
00:08:32,278 --> 00:08:33,546
The more I read, the more nervous I get.

173
00:08:36,515 --> 00:08:37,183
Don't be.

174
00:08:37,717 --> 00:08:38,684
Long Quan also said

175
00:08:38,784 --> 00:08:40,519
it's only a minor procedure under local anesthesia.

176
00:08:40,953 --> 00:08:41,587
Don't worry.

177
00:08:42,989 --> 00:08:43,890
Who's Long Quan?

178
00:08:44,123 --> 00:08:44,891
Long Quan is...

179
00:08:48,995 --> 00:08:50,096
Long Quan is...

180
00:08:50,129 --> 00:08:51,998
Long Jiaojiao from my room.

181
00:08:53,065 --> 00:08:55,368
At school, we called her Long Quan.

182
00:08:56,168 --> 00:08:58,204
We were classmates.

183
00:08:58,838 --> 00:09:00,640
Who would've thought that after all these years,

184
00:09:00,873 --> 00:09:02,808
we'd meet again in this ward

185
00:09:02,808 --> 00:09:04,810
as fellow patients?

186
00:09:06,245 --> 00:09:07,747
Time really flies.

187
00:09:10,016 --> 00:09:10,383
Here?

188
00:09:10,516 --> 00:09:11,517
I sign here, right?

189
00:09:11,651 --> 00:09:11,984
Yes.

190
00:09:14,086 --> 00:09:15,354
Don't judge me

191
00:09:15,354 --> 00:09:16,355
by how I look now.

192
00:09:16,856 --> 00:09:17,957
Back in school,

193
00:09:18,157 --> 00:09:19,926
I was prettier than Long Quan.

194
00:09:20,126 --> 00:09:21,394
I had a better figure too.

195
00:09:21,627 --> 00:09:22,929
I was also

196
00:09:22,995 --> 00:09:24,063
the best dancer in our class.

197
00:09:24,363 --> 00:09:25,398
I took her with me

198
00:09:25,531 --> 00:09:27,166
to represent our school

199
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:29,235
in a district-wide dance competition,

200
00:09:29,335 --> 00:09:30,670
and we came third.

201
00:09:30,803 --> 00:09:32,305
It was even in the newspaper.

202
00:09:32,638 --> 00:09:33,239
Really?

203
00:09:33,272 --> 00:09:34,006
Really.

204
00:09:34,073 --> 00:09:35,041
What dance did you perform?

205
00:09:35,207 --> 00:09:36,208
A Dai dance.

206
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:46,085
All right, enough.

207
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:47,520
Don't overdo it before surgery.

208
00:09:47,553 --> 00:09:48,287
Sign and go back.

209
00:09:48,354 --> 00:09:49,388
I'm just trying

210
00:09:49,455 --> 00:09:50,523
to loosen up.

211
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:51,691
The moment you mention signing,

212
00:09:51,691 --> 00:09:53,192
my hand starts shaking again.

213
00:09:53,893 --> 00:09:54,827
Sis, don't be nervous.

214
00:09:55,027 --> 00:09:55,595
Trust us.

215
00:09:55,928 --> 00:09:56,395
Okay.

216
00:09:58,230 --> 00:09:59,465
Look how kind Dr. Du is.

217
00:09:59,599 --> 00:10:00,566
Such a good young man.

218
00:10:00,866 --> 00:10:03,202
Whenever I see you, I think,

219
00:10:03,603 --> 00:10:05,304
why is our Long Quan in such a rush?

220
00:10:05,371 --> 00:10:06,706
There are so many good young men

221
00:10:06,706 --> 00:10:07,606
waiting for her.

222
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:11,277
What's wrong with her?

223
00:10:12,211 --> 00:10:12,645
Right here.

224
00:10:12,712 --> 00:10:13,079
She...

225
00:10:14,513 --> 00:10:15,715
She broke up.

226
00:10:17,249 --> 00:10:18,651
Good. Wonderful.

227
00:10:19,318 --> 00:10:20,720
That stupid baboon.

228
00:10:22,722 --> 00:10:23,923
Thank you for bringing her here.

229
00:10:24,357 --> 00:10:25,691
Her consciousness and breathing are fine.

230
00:10:25,791 --> 00:10:26,959
She's just emotionally unstable.

231
00:10:27,693 --> 00:10:28,961
She insisted we close the curtain.

232
00:10:29,195 --> 00:10:29,962
From what I heard,

233
00:10:30,229 --> 00:10:31,464
her boyfriend upset her.

234
00:10:33,933 --> 00:10:34,734
Thank you, Director Kong.

235
00:10:34,767 --> 00:10:35,968
I'll take her back to the ward shortly.

236
00:10:36,202 --> 00:10:36,469
All right.

237
00:10:36,769 --> 00:10:37,603
Sorry to trouble you, Dr. Fang.

238
00:10:37,770 --> 00:10:38,270
It's fine.

239
00:10:44,810 --> 00:10:45,411
Jiaojiao.

240
00:10:46,345 --> 00:10:47,146
Are you okay?

241
00:10:50,316 --> 00:10:51,450
I'll take you back to the ward.

242
00:11:13,172 --> 00:11:14,774
You saw me have a seizure, didn't you?

243
00:11:18,411 --> 00:11:19,912
Was it frightening?

244
00:11:21,013 --> 00:11:21,847
No.

245
00:11:22,548 --> 00:11:24,116
I work in the ICU every day.

246
00:11:24,450 --> 00:11:24,884
Think about it.

247
00:11:24,917 --> 00:11:26,285
The things I see daily...

248
00:11:26,852 --> 00:11:28,254
For us doctors,

249
00:11:28,654 --> 00:11:29,488
a patient being sick

250
00:11:29,488 --> 00:11:30,589
is nothing frightening.

251
00:11:32,558 --> 00:11:33,626
In the café,

252
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:35,161
was anyone filming?

253
00:11:37,963 --> 00:11:39,532
Sorry, I really didn't notice.

254
00:11:42,835 --> 00:11:44,470
Was that man just now your boyfriend?

255
00:11:48,207 --> 00:11:49,642
I've been hospitalized this long,

256
00:11:50,142 --> 00:11:51,544
and this was his first visit.

257
00:11:53,512 --> 00:11:54,947
How long have you been together?

258
00:11:55,414 --> 00:11:56,148
Four years.

259
00:11:56,916 --> 00:11:58,384
He's the only person

260
00:11:59,685 --> 00:12:00,920
who's seen me have a seizure

261
00:12:01,954 --> 00:12:03,989
and still stayed with me.

262
00:12:05,424 --> 00:12:07,626
She may look fierce

263
00:12:07,693 --> 00:12:08,527
and strong on the outside,

264
00:12:08,561 --> 00:12:10,429
but she's actually very fragile inside.

265
00:12:10,629 --> 00:12:11,664
I know her.

266
00:12:13,199 --> 00:12:14,667
Back in school,

267
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:16,869
she was nothing like this.

268
00:12:17,169 --> 00:12:18,437
One time after school...

269
00:12:18,604 --> 00:12:19,271
Zhang Diao'e.

270
00:12:19,305 --> 00:12:19,839
Me?

271
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:22,074
Go back and rest.

272
00:12:23,375 --> 00:12:24,710
We're just chatting

273
00:12:24,810 --> 00:12:26,412
to calm her down.

274
00:12:27,279 --> 00:12:28,314
In this office,

275
00:12:28,414 --> 00:12:29,548
you're the most serious one.

276
00:12:30,249 --> 00:12:31,984
I'll go calm myself down.

277
00:12:41,961 --> 00:12:42,495
Jiaojiao.

278
00:12:43,763 --> 00:12:44,330
Dr. Fang.

279
00:12:44,563 --> 00:12:45,397
I want to give you

280
00:12:45,397 --> 00:12:46,198
another physical exam.

281
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:49,168
Didn't you already do one?

282
00:12:49,168 --> 00:12:50,202
That young Dr. Ye

283
00:12:50,202 --> 00:12:50,836
examined me last time.

284
00:12:51,003 --> 00:12:51,470
I know.

285
00:12:51,871 --> 00:12:52,638
But your lumbar puncture

286
00:12:52,671 --> 00:12:53,672
results only came back

287
00:12:53,706 --> 00:12:54,774
in full yesterday.

288
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:56,041
Sometimes a condition

289
00:12:56,041 --> 00:12:57,409
changes over time.

290
00:12:57,676 --> 00:12:59,245
So I want to examine you carefully again.

291
00:12:59,512 --> 00:13:00,846
Maybe we'll find something new.

292
00:13:03,783 --> 00:13:04,183
All right.

293
00:13:08,721 --> 00:13:09,889
Let me show you something.

294
00:13:13,759 --> 00:13:14,193
What?

295
00:13:18,798 --> 00:13:20,032
How did you get this?

296
00:13:20,266 --> 00:13:21,734
Zhang Diao'e told me

297
00:13:21,767 --> 00:13:22,601
you two learned dance together

298
00:13:22,635 --> 00:13:23,636
when you were young

299
00:13:23,636 --> 00:13:24,603
and even won an award.

300
00:13:25,104 --> 00:13:26,238
I searched for ages

301
00:13:26,305 --> 00:13:27,840
before I found this article.

302
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:30,543
That big mouth Zhang Diao'e.

303
00:13:30,709 --> 00:13:31,844
But she wasn't wrong.

304
00:13:32,244 --> 00:13:33,479
You've always been beautiful.

305
00:13:34,113 --> 00:13:34,713
Long Quan.

306
00:13:43,756 --> 00:13:44,523
Come on, lie down.

307
00:13:46,592 --> 00:13:47,326
Tell me

308
00:13:47,359 --> 00:13:48,160
if anything feels uncomfortable.

309
00:13:57,636 --> 00:13:58,170
Does it hurt?

310
00:13:58,837 --> 00:13:59,405
No.

311
00:14:05,311 --> 00:14:05,911
Look.

312
00:14:06,712 --> 00:14:08,047
You're the one who's sick,

313
00:14:09,515 --> 00:14:10,516
and you're still the one who's beautiful.

314
00:14:11,750 --> 00:14:13,185
Whether it's your illness

315
00:14:13,652 --> 00:14:14,720
or your relationships,

316
00:14:15,487 --> 00:14:16,855
just be brave and be yourself.

317
00:14:17,990 --> 00:14:18,324
Come on.

318
00:14:19,191 --> 00:14:19,892
Bend your leg.

319
00:14:20,392 --> 00:14:21,193
I'm going to apply some pressure.

320
00:14:23,596 --> 00:14:24,597
Any discomfort?

321
00:14:27,066 --> 00:14:28,033
No.

322
00:14:28,667 --> 00:14:29,134
Do your joints usually

323
00:14:31,570 --> 00:14:32,905
feel uncomfortable?

324
00:14:32,905 --> 00:14:34,240
No.

325
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:35,441
Have you ever noticed

326
00:14:39,712 --> 00:14:41,413
any rashes

327
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:42,681
or nodules?

328
00:14:42,748 --> 00:14:44,149
Epilepsy is a brain disease.

329
00:14:46,085 --> 00:14:47,953
What could it have to do with my skin?

330
00:14:48,087 --> 00:14:49,889
Dr. Fang,

331
00:14:51,123 --> 00:14:51,624
I know you're trying to help me

332
00:14:51,624 --> 00:14:53,425
find the cause,

333
00:14:53,692 --> 00:14:54,226
but

334
00:14:54,894 --> 00:14:55,894
maybe we should just forget it.

335
00:14:55,995 --> 00:14:56,662
Some illnesses

336
00:14:56,795 --> 00:14:58,163
don't show when they're mild.

337
00:14:58,230 --> 00:14:58,797
Once they become serious,

338
00:14:58,831 --> 00:15:00,266
the symptoms naturally appear.

339
00:15:00,366 --> 00:15:01,367
We can't wait for that.

340
00:15:01,433 --> 00:15:03,969
By then, treatment may be delayed.

341
00:15:07,573 --> 00:15:08,774
It's okay. Leave it to us.

342
00:15:11,877 --> 00:15:12,845
Let's get you some air.

343
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:15,447
Pull it to there.

344
00:15:16,949 --> 00:15:17,449
Like this?

345
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:18,751
Yes.

346
00:15:19,752 --> 00:15:20,586
Sorry.

347
00:15:20,753 --> 00:15:22,588
My face is sensitive.

348
00:15:25,324 --> 00:15:26,492
It turns red in the sun.

349
00:15:26,959 --> 00:15:27,760
Does it get very red?

350
00:15:27,793 --> 00:15:29,561
Not usually.

351
00:15:29,995 --> 00:15:31,797
It normally fades quickly.

352
00:15:32,064 --> 00:15:33,132
There was one time at the beach, though.

353
00:15:33,132 --> 00:15:33,999
That episode was worse.

354
00:15:34,967 --> 00:15:36,535
It took half a month to fade.

355
00:15:38,971 --> 00:15:40,406
What did the redness look like?

356
00:15:40,773 --> 00:15:42,775
It didn't hurt or itch.

357
00:15:43,242 --> 00:15:46,078
It looked like sunburn makeup,

358
00:15:46,512 --> 00:15:47,646
from my nose across my cheekbones,

359
00:15:48,947 --> 00:15:49,915
like a butterfly.

360
00:15:51,183 --> 00:15:51,550
Do you have a photo?

361
00:15:55,654 --> 00:15:56,155
Yes.

362
00:16:22,948 --> 00:16:24,149
This one.

363
00:16:24,450 --> 00:16:24,950
What's wrong? Are you uncomfortable?

364
00:16:25,150 --> 00:16:26,318
I'm cold.

365
00:16:26,452 --> 00:16:27,720
Lying here

366
00:16:28,787 --> 00:16:30,155
also makes me a little scared.

367
00:16:30,356 --> 00:16:31,223
It's only a minor procedure.

368
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:32,624
The incision

369
00:16:34,293 --> 00:16:36,395
will be about the size of a fingernail.

370
00:16:36,929 --> 00:16:38,230
I'm just timid.

371
00:16:38,230 --> 00:16:39,064
I was the same

372
00:16:39,431 --> 00:16:40,666
when I gave birth to Tingting.

373
00:16:40,666 --> 00:16:41,533
Lying here exposed,

374
00:16:44,570 --> 00:16:45,104
I started shaking.

375
00:16:45,204 --> 00:16:46,205
Keep your hand in.

376
00:16:46,672 --> 00:16:47,673
It's itchy here.

377
00:16:47,906 --> 00:16:49,008
You can't reach out again.

378
00:16:52,911 --> 00:16:54,046
We just finished draping you.

379
00:16:54,146 --> 00:16:55,447
If I keep shaking like this,

380
00:16:56,615 --> 00:16:57,883
could the needle go in crooked?

381
00:17:02,588 --> 00:17:03,889
I still can't control it.

382
00:17:04,690 --> 00:17:06,091
Tell me about your daughters.

383
00:17:06,525 --> 00:17:07,092
I have two daughters.

384
00:17:09,328 --> 00:17:10,696
My older daughter...

385
00:17:12,965 --> 00:17:15,134
My older one is Panpan.

386
00:17:16,001 --> 00:17:17,102
Our Panpan is very promising.

387
00:17:17,102 --> 00:17:18,404
Every year, she brings home

388
00:17:18,637 --> 00:17:20,406
so many certificates and awards.

389
00:17:20,472 --> 00:17:21,306
Parents like us—

390
00:17:21,306 --> 00:17:22,975
how did we ever have

391
00:17:24,510 --> 00:17:25,444
such a wonderful daughter?

392
00:17:25,477 --> 00:17:26,945
Sometimes

393
00:17:27,413 --> 00:17:28,680
when I look at you, I think

394
00:17:28,847 --> 00:17:30,449
maybe when my daughter grows up,

395
00:17:30,549 --> 00:17:31,750
she can become as successful

396
00:17:34,553 --> 00:17:36,455
as the pretty doctor.

397
00:17:36,688 --> 00:17:38,791
She's good at every subject.

398
00:17:40,592 --> 00:17:41,827
Her teachers all adore her.

399
00:17:41,927 --> 00:17:43,295
This time, I guess Mom

400
00:17:44,663 --> 00:17:46,765
is setting an example for her too.

401
00:17:47,232 --> 00:17:48,333
Who would've thought

402
00:17:48,667 --> 00:17:50,002
a patient

403
00:17:51,870 --> 00:17:53,272
could still be useful?

404
00:17:53,872 --> 00:17:54,840
Didn't Director Zhou say

405
00:17:55,107 --> 00:17:56,308
that with this livestream,

406
00:17:57,109 --> 00:17:58,043
all of you can learn?

407
00:17:58,710 --> 00:18:00,879
Pretty doctor,

408
00:18:01,547 --> 00:18:02,214
watch carefully and learn well.

409
00:18:03,048 --> 00:18:04,683
Someday,

410
00:18:07,152 --> 00:18:07,686
you can become a chief too.

411
00:18:08,454 --> 00:18:09,288
Sure.

412
00:18:09,288 --> 00:18:10,289
Our chief

413
00:18:10,923 --> 00:18:12,424
is the one doing your procedure.

414
00:18:12,591 --> 00:18:13,592
Director Zhou is very skilled.

415
00:18:14,126 --> 00:18:14,927
I'll be here too.

416
00:18:14,927 --> 00:18:15,694
Later, we'll also give you

417
00:18:15,828 --> 00:18:17,196
some anesthetic.

418
00:18:19,598 --> 00:18:21,266
It won't hurt that much.

419
00:18:21,967 --> 00:18:22,935
I could tell long ago.

420
00:18:23,769 --> 00:18:25,437
Pretty doctor,

421
00:18:26,305 --> 00:18:27,773
you look cold on the outside,

422
00:18:42,988 --> 00:18:43,655
Zhang Diao'e.

423
00:18:44,756 --> 00:18:45,424
Are you ready?

424
00:18:45,924 --> 00:18:46,592
We'll begin shortly.

425
00:18:47,359 --> 00:18:47,993
Director Zhou,

426
00:18:48,727 --> 00:18:50,329
I'm not wearing makeup.

427
00:18:50,629 --> 00:18:51,463
Don't film my face.

428
00:18:52,197 --> 00:18:52,798
We won't.

429
00:18:53,432 --> 00:18:54,233
Just like you said,

430
00:18:54,766 --> 00:18:55,934
with so many machines watching,

431
00:18:56,468 --> 00:18:57,636
I'll definitely do this carefully.

432
00:18:58,370 --> 00:18:59,271
I trust you.

433
00:19:22,895 --> 00:19:24,263
The angiography confirms our assessment.

434
00:19:24,396 --> 00:19:25,364
The preoperative contrast-enhanced

435
00:19:25,364 --> 00:19:25,931
CT scan

436
00:19:25,964 --> 00:19:27,032
identified the lesions

437
00:19:27,032 --> 00:19:27,799
in the left lower lobe.

438
00:19:27,866 --> 00:19:29,201
pulmonary arteriovenous malformations

439
00:19:29,568 --> 00:19:30,502
Next, based on

440
00:19:30,502 --> 00:19:31,470
the location of each lesion,

441
00:19:31,570 --> 00:19:32,638
we'll perform selective angiography.

442
00:19:36,041 --> 00:19:37,743
Selective angiography really tests

443
00:19:37,743 --> 00:19:38,810
the operator's judgment

444
00:19:38,877 --> 00:19:40,012
and precision.

445
00:19:40,145 --> 00:19:41,847
In a lung segment the size of a finger,

446
00:19:42,080 --> 00:19:43,749
we have to find the abnormal vessel

447
00:19:43,916 --> 00:19:44,783
while also making sure

448
00:19:44,850 --> 00:19:45,751
the surrounding normal vessels

449
00:19:45,851 --> 00:19:47,519
aren't affected.

450
00:19:47,686 --> 00:19:49,555
The catheter has to be advanced

451
00:19:49,555 --> 00:19:50,255
to the lesion with extreme accuracy

452
00:19:50,322 --> 00:19:51,390
to minimize

453
00:19:51,523 --> 00:19:52,357
any residual shunt.

454
00:19:54,493 --> 00:19:56,728
It's like trying to catch a mouse

455
00:19:56,995 --> 00:19:57,863
without breaking the china.

456
00:19:57,863 --> 00:19:59,164
Imagine a room

457
00:19:59,198 --> 00:20:00,265
filled with valuable porcelain,

458
00:20:00,766 --> 00:20:01,967
but suddenly

459
00:20:02,034 --> 00:20:02,868
a few mice appear.

460
00:20:03,001 --> 00:20:03,602
We have to catch every mouse

461
00:20:03,602 --> 00:20:04,503
inside that cramped space

462
00:20:04,603 --> 00:20:05,971
without damaging

463
00:20:06,204 --> 00:20:07,105
a single piece of porcelain.

464
00:20:07,105 --> 00:20:08,106
any single piece of porcelain.

465
00:20:08,607 --> 00:20:09,274
My God.

466
00:20:09,441 --> 00:20:10,209
That's so difficult.

467
00:20:10,475 --> 00:20:12,144
Yeah, incredibly difficult.

468
00:20:12,311 --> 00:20:12,878
Keep learning.

469
00:20:13,278 --> 00:20:14,112
There's always more to learn.

470
00:20:58,490 --> 00:20:59,358
The vascular plug is in position.

471
00:21:03,495 --> 00:21:04,062
It's occluded.

472
00:21:08,600 --> 00:21:09,434
Don't look at the screen yet.

473
00:21:09,835 --> 00:21:10,402
Listen first.

474
00:21:22,314 --> 00:21:24,483
Her oxygen saturation

475
00:21:24,483 --> 00:21:25,350
should be above 85 now.

476
00:21:30,722 --> 00:21:31,890
It's 87.

477
00:21:35,394 --> 00:21:36,161
Really?

478
00:21:36,328 --> 00:21:37,496
That's amazing.

479
00:21:40,532 --> 00:21:41,767
Is it really that mysterious?

480
00:21:43,935 --> 00:21:45,203
How did you know?

481
00:21:45,837 --> 00:21:46,872
At different heart rates

482
00:21:47,072 --> 00:21:48,173
and oxygen saturation levels,

483
00:21:48,707 --> 00:21:49,441
the monitor sounds

484
00:21:49,508 --> 00:21:50,242
different too.

485
00:21:50,442 --> 00:21:52,277
When oxygen is high, the tone is sharper.

486
00:21:52,477 --> 00:21:54,212
When it's low, the tone is duller.

487
00:21:54,546 --> 00:21:55,747
During an intervention,

488
00:21:55,914 --> 00:21:57,416
we don't just train our hands and eyes.

489
00:21:57,683 --> 00:21:58,483
We train our ears too.

490
00:21:59,184 --> 00:21:59,851
The monitor

491
00:22:00,152 --> 00:22:01,453
can give you a lot of information.

492
00:22:02,087 --> 00:22:02,921
When you're operating

493
00:22:02,921 --> 00:22:03,989
with your hands,

494
00:22:04,556 --> 00:22:05,624
you can't keep taking your eyes away

495
00:22:05,691 --> 00:22:06,725
to stare at the screen.

496
00:22:07,492 --> 00:22:09,094
That's when distinguishing sounds

497
00:22:09,094 --> 00:22:10,295
becomes extremely important.

498
00:22:10,962 --> 00:22:11,830
Once you've heard enough, you know.

499
00:22:12,531 --> 00:22:13,432
The monitor's sounds

500
00:22:13,665 --> 00:22:14,833
can tell you a great deal.

501
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:16,635
For example,

502
00:22:16,635 --> 00:22:17,836
you can hear

503
00:22:18,203 --> 00:22:19,471
the irregular rhythm of premature beats.

504
00:22:19,671 --> 00:22:20,305
President Wang.

505
00:22:20,572 --> 00:22:21,640
I always emphasize this point

506
00:22:21,640 --> 00:22:22,441
to my students.

507
00:22:22,874 --> 00:22:23,475
Unfortunately,

508
00:22:23,709 --> 00:22:24,476
the younger generation

509
00:22:24,910 --> 00:22:25,944
rarely takes it seriously.

510
00:22:26,278 --> 00:22:27,713
It's become an old-school craft.

511
00:22:28,413 --> 00:22:30,115
Now you don't have to worry it'll be lost.

512
00:22:30,449 --> 00:22:31,383
This proves

513
00:22:31,516 --> 00:22:32,517
that even with such new technology,

514
00:22:32,584 --> 00:22:34,353
classic skills still matter.

515
00:22:35,053 --> 00:22:35,520
Exactly.

516
00:22:36,088 --> 00:22:37,022
No wonder someone so young

517
00:22:37,122 --> 00:22:38,190
could become head of a major department.

518
00:22:38,590 --> 00:22:39,991
You really have the skills.

519
00:22:44,062 --> 00:22:44,730
Deployment complete.

520
00:22:53,872 --> 00:22:54,639
How do you feel?

521
00:22:55,307 --> 00:22:56,608
Is breathing much easier?

522
00:22:58,844 --> 00:22:59,511
Much better.

523
00:23:00,679 --> 00:23:01,346
Much smoother.

524
00:23:02,881 --> 00:23:04,549
It feels like a huge sandbag

525
00:23:04,549 --> 00:23:05,717
was lifted off my chest.

526
00:23:07,486 --> 00:23:08,487
I blocked the largest one first.

527
00:23:08,487 --> 00:23:09,354
Once the others are treated,

528
00:23:09,855 --> 00:23:10,922
you'll feel completely different.

529
00:23:11,123 --> 00:23:12,324
Thank you, Director Zhou.

530
00:23:14,192 --> 00:23:15,560
Your lips already look rosier.

531
00:23:22,634 --> 00:23:24,069
Thank you, pretty doctor.

532
00:23:34,746 --> 00:23:36,715
I've worked with him

533
00:23:55,834 --> 00:23:57,002
on TAVR procedures

534
00:23:57,002 --> 00:23:57,469
and hybrid operations,

535
00:23:57,502 --> 00:23:58,036
but I never knew

536
00:23:58,103 --> 00:23:58,670
he had a skill like this up his sleeve.

537
00:23:58,703 --> 00:24:00,105
He really showed off.

538
00:24:00,439 --> 00:24:01,606
By the way,

539
00:24:02,774 --> 00:24:03,275
I think I know

540
00:24:03,875 --> 00:24:04,709
what caused Long Jiaojiao's illness.

541
00:24:04,709 --> 00:24:05,844
Hello, everyone.

542
00:24:09,848 --> 00:24:11,016
Jiaojiao is live.

543
00:24:11,016 --> 00:24:12,451
So many of you

544
00:24:15,120 --> 00:24:15,754
joined the moment I came on.

545
00:24:15,754 --> 00:24:17,255
Love you all.

546
00:24:17,689 --> 00:24:18,623
Yes.

547
00:24:20,892 --> 00:24:21,393
I'm still in the hospital.

548
00:24:22,093 --> 00:24:23,094
I really shouldn't be livestreaming here,

549
00:24:24,729 --> 00:24:26,464
but there are some things

550
00:24:26,631 --> 00:24:27,732
I truly want to share.

551
00:24:27,732 --> 00:24:28,934
Yes.

552
00:24:30,569 --> 00:24:30,869
I also got the hospital's permission.

553
00:24:31,503 --> 00:24:33,205
Yes.

554
00:24:35,907 --> 00:24:36,374
Those were epileptic seizures.

555
00:24:37,209 --> 00:24:38,410
So today,

556
00:24:41,112 --> 00:24:42,280
I want to tell

557
00:24:42,948 --> 00:24:43,915
everyone who cares about Jiaojiao

558
00:24:43,949 --> 00:24:45,784
that I'm sick.

559
00:24:46,751 --> 00:24:47,652
This illness has troubled me

560
00:24:49,554 --> 00:24:51,089
for a very long time.

561
00:24:51,089 --> 00:24:52,023
Not only physically,

562
00:24:52,824 --> 00:24:54,092
but even more psychologically.

563
00:24:54,759 --> 00:24:56,127
Thank you.

564
00:25:01,333 --> 00:25:01,766
And

565
00:25:02,567 --> 00:25:03,134
I also want to thank the doctors here.

566
00:25:03,168 --> 00:25:05,670
They followed through to the end,

567
00:25:06,304 --> 00:25:08,106
carefully ruling things out

568
00:25:08,273 --> 00:25:09,674
step by step,

569
00:25:09,708 --> 00:25:10,509
and finally helped me find

570
00:25:10,642 --> 00:25:12,244
the cause of my recurrent seizures

571
00:25:12,310 --> 00:25:14,012
and the source of my heart attack.

572
00:25:14,079 --> 00:25:16,047
So

573
00:25:16,815 --> 00:25:17,315
Long Jiaojiao's heart attack and seizures

574
00:25:17,883 --> 00:25:20,852
were both caused by lupus.

575
00:25:20,852 --> 00:25:22,754
Right.

576
00:25:22,988 --> 00:25:23,355
Her early symptoms

577
00:25:23,688 --> 00:25:24,823
were atypical.

578
00:25:24,923 --> 00:25:25,590
Several key markers

579
00:25:25,757 --> 00:25:27,125
were either negative

580
00:25:27,158 --> 00:25:28,226
or only weakly positive.

581
00:25:28,226 --> 00:25:29,427
The disease was both hidden and misleading.

582
00:25:29,995 --> 00:25:31,663
That's why no one

583
00:25:31,796 --> 00:25:32,564
thought in that direction.

584
00:25:32,564 --> 00:25:33,531
Impressive, Dr. Fang.

585
00:25:33,798 --> 00:25:35,033
How did you figure it out?

586
00:25:35,367 --> 00:25:36,334
Didn't you and Ouyang say

587
00:25:36,968 --> 00:25:38,436
many indicators need repeated testing?

588
00:25:38,603 --> 00:25:40,205
So I gave her

589
00:25:40,472 --> 00:25:41,373
another physical examination.

590
00:25:41,373 --> 00:25:42,774
I noticed her face turns red in sunlight.

591
00:25:43,074 --> 00:25:44,843
Then I compared that

592
00:25:45,210 --> 00:25:46,611
with her previous results,

593
00:25:46,611 --> 00:25:47,345
and the answer became clear.

594
00:25:47,479 --> 00:25:48,146
How is she reacting now?

595
00:25:48,547 --> 00:25:50,115
Surprisingly calm.

596
00:25:50,582 --> 00:25:51,883
Really?

597
00:25:53,285 --> 00:25:54,185
She'll need steroids

598
00:25:55,153 --> 00:25:55,987
for this condition.

599
00:25:55,987 --> 00:25:57,088
She cares so much about her appearance.

600
00:25:58,189 --> 00:25:59,357
Did you explain it clearly?

601
00:25:59,791 --> 00:26:00,759
Of course.

602
00:26:00,959 --> 00:26:02,394
These days, treatment usually combines steroids

603
00:26:02,827 --> 00:26:04,329
with immunosuppressants.

604
00:26:04,362 --> 00:26:05,397
As long as the dosage is controlled

605
00:26:05,430 --> 00:26:06,331
and she follows instructions strictly,

606
00:26:06,464 --> 00:26:07,866
weight gain isn't inevitable.

607
00:26:07,933 --> 00:26:08,800
And I think

608
00:26:09,034 --> 00:26:10,168
her emotional burden is gone now.

609
00:26:11,303 --> 00:26:12,370
For her,

610
00:26:12,504 --> 00:26:14,039
any physical problem

611
00:26:14,205 --> 00:26:15,106
is no longer that frightening.

612
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:16,641
You all saw

613
00:26:16,708 --> 00:26:17,809
how ugly

614
00:26:18,510 --> 00:26:19,411
and frightening I looked during a seizure.

615
00:26:19,711 --> 00:26:21,880
That's also why

616
00:26:22,514 --> 00:26:23,148
I never had the courage

617
00:26:23,515 --> 00:26:24,482
to tell you.

618
00:26:25,850 --> 00:26:26,952
But my friend Zhang Diao'e

619
00:26:27,052 --> 00:26:28,186
told me

620
00:26:28,887 --> 00:26:30,755
that having a seizure

621
00:26:30,755 --> 00:26:31,823
isn't my fault.

622
00:26:33,224 --> 00:26:33,892
If someone dislikes me because of it,

623
00:26:34,826 --> 00:26:35,760
then I also have the right

624
00:26:36,394 --> 00:26:37,796
not to like them.

625
00:26:37,829 --> 00:26:38,630
And there was also Dr. Fang,

626
00:26:38,997 --> 00:26:39,965
a very lovely doctor.

627
00:26:39,998 --> 00:26:41,232
She told me

628
00:26:43,768 --> 00:26:45,303
to be brave and be myself.

629
00:26:45,837 --> 00:26:47,472
So

630
00:26:47,672 --> 00:26:48,506
I truly feel

631
00:26:48,974 --> 00:26:50,442
as if I've been given a new life.

632
00:26:51,209 --> 00:26:51,676
The friend I just mentioned,

633
00:26:52,110 --> 00:26:53,945
Zhang Diao'e,

634
00:26:54,646 --> 00:26:55,914
was my middle-school classmate.

635
00:26:57,749 --> 00:26:59,050
Who would've thought

636
00:26:59,084 --> 00:26:59,718
we'd meet again in a hospital

637
00:26:59,851 --> 00:27:01,453
after so many years?

638
00:27:02,921 --> 00:27:04,522
But at first,

639
00:27:04,522 --> 00:27:06,124
what she feared most

640
00:27:08,026 --> 00:27:09,227
wasn't her illness.

641
00:27:10,095 --> 00:27:10,895
It was that she hadn't had a son.

642
00:27:10,895 --> 00:27:11,796
Yes.

643
00:27:12,230 --> 00:27:13,531
I'm from the countryside too.

644
00:27:14,866 --> 00:27:15,333
Growing up, I saw

645
00:27:15,767 --> 00:27:16,935
and heard about

646
00:27:17,802 --> 00:27:19,437
many, many women

647
00:27:19,471 --> 00:27:20,171
like Zhang Diao'e.

648
00:27:20,271 --> 00:27:21,172
They had no residential land,

649
00:27:21,239 --> 00:27:22,707
so they had no home.

650
00:27:23,008 --> 00:27:24,209
They had no contracted farmland,

651
00:27:24,209 --> 00:27:25,143
so they had no way to make a living.

652
00:27:25,510 --> 00:27:26,311
This is called patrilocal residence.

653
00:27:26,344 --> 00:27:27,545
I don't know whether

654
00:27:27,946 --> 00:27:29,314
you've heard that term.

655
00:27:29,614 --> 00:27:30,482
Whenever I think of Zhang Diao'e now,

656
00:27:30,482 --> 00:27:31,449
I think of it.

657
00:27:32,150 --> 00:27:34,119
No way to survive.

658
00:27:34,152 --> 00:27:35,186
Nowhere to go.

659
00:27:35,553 --> 00:27:36,521
They can only

660
00:27:36,721 --> 00:27:37,555
live with their husband's family.

661
00:27:38,089 --> 00:27:38,723
Failing to bear a son

662
00:27:38,757 --> 00:27:40,325
becomes their crime.

663
00:27:41,793 --> 00:27:42,394
And if they end up with

664
00:27:42,427 --> 00:27:43,762
an unreliable or abusive husband,

665
00:27:44,562 --> 00:27:45,230
they can only swallow their anger

666
00:27:45,330 --> 00:27:46,431
and endure everything.

667
00:27:46,998 --> 00:27:48,466
I hope the relevant authorities

668
00:27:48,733 --> 00:27:49,567
can see them.

669
00:27:51,102 --> 00:27:52,303
Every Zhang Diao'e

670
00:27:52,303 --> 00:27:53,238
should have land.

671
00:27:54,472 --> 00:27:55,507
They should be able to live

672
00:27:55,573 --> 00:27:56,808
with dignity

673
00:27:57,275 --> 00:27:58,476
and confidence.

674
00:27:58,543 --> 00:27:59,678
Dr. Fang, look.

675
00:28:14,692 --> 00:28:16,294
My lips

676
00:28:16,594 --> 00:28:17,729
used to look like

677
00:28:17,962 --> 00:28:18,596
a purple sweet potato left out for days.

678
00:28:18,596 --> 00:28:20,031
Now look at them.

679
00:28:20,031 --> 00:28:21,232
Don't they look like

680
00:28:21,566 --> 00:28:22,667
fresh peaches picked in midsummer?

681
00:28:23,334 --> 00:28:24,636
That's wonderful.

682
00:28:24,636 --> 00:28:25,770
I barely recognize myself.

683
00:28:27,405 --> 00:28:28,106
This is a good gift.

684
00:28:28,973 --> 00:28:30,809
Good. Good.

685
00:28:31,643 --> 00:28:32,644
And this.

686
00:28:34,479 --> 00:28:35,280
Many women can only

687
00:28:36,548 --> 00:28:37,282
live with their husband's family.

688
00:28:38,650 --> 00:28:39,584
Failing to bear a son

689
00:28:39,584 --> 00:28:40,919
becomes their crime.

690
00:28:41,486 --> 00:28:42,120
I want to tell Zhang Diao'e:

691
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:43,488
don't feel inferior

692
00:28:43,988 --> 00:28:45,323
just because you haven't had a son.

693
00:28:46,558 --> 00:28:47,959
She's talking about me.

694
00:28:48,093 --> 00:28:49,127
The rights you deserve

695
00:28:51,362 --> 00:28:51,629
shouldn't be trampled on

696
00:28:51,629 --> 00:28:52,564
or ignored.

697
00:28:52,664 --> 00:28:53,531
Every Zhang Diao'e

698
00:28:53,798 --> 00:28:54,732
should have

699
00:28:55,733 --> 00:28:56,735
land of her own.

700
00:28:56,735 --> 00:28:57,569
They should live with dignity

701
00:28:57,569 --> 00:28:58,503
and confidence.

702
00:28:59,037 --> 00:29:00,305
Zhang Diao'e,

703
00:29:00,371 --> 00:29:01,473
you are no one's accessory.

704
00:29:02,273 --> 00:29:02,974
Your life belongs to you.

705
00:29:03,675 --> 00:29:04,976
I'll always be here.

706
00:29:05,677 --> 00:29:07,212
Keep going.

707
00:29:08,713 --> 00:29:09,614
Focus on your livestream.

708
00:29:11,216 --> 00:29:11,649
Why did you mention me?

709
00:29:12,350 --> 00:29:13,585
I'm here to give you a like.

710
00:29:13,651 --> 00:29:14,919
Feels good.

711
00:29:16,488 --> 00:29:17,689
Director.

712
00:29:41,746 --> 00:29:42,614
May I sit here?

713
00:29:55,126 --> 00:29:55,527
Of course.

714
00:30:08,807 --> 00:30:09,607
Do you always eat this fast?

715
00:30:13,044 --> 00:30:13,511
I'm a little hungry.

716
00:30:42,507 --> 00:30:43,708
I saw Zhang Diao'e

717
00:30:48,746 --> 00:30:49,714
was transferred to the general ward.

718
00:31:01,893 --> 00:31:02,827
I just checked on her.

719
00:31:03,294 --> 00:31:04,229
She's settled in

720
00:31:06,064 --> 00:31:07,565
and recovering well.

721
00:31:07,865 --> 00:31:08,666
She seems to like you.

722
00:31:08,666 --> 00:31:09,767
Does she?

723
00:31:13,805 --> 00:31:14,973
It feels about the same as everyone else.

724
00:31:17,442 --> 00:31:18,042
I've heard so many thank-yous

725
00:31:20,078 --> 00:31:21,279
that I'm used to it.

726
00:31:22,947 --> 00:31:23,948
No.

727
00:31:24,582 --> 00:31:25,183
As doctors,

728
00:31:26,918 --> 00:31:27,352
we hear

729
00:31:32,490 --> 00:31:33,224
a lot of gratitude every day.

730
00:31:34,158 --> 00:31:35,159
Some effort

731
00:31:35,159 --> 00:31:35,927
may not be acknowledged,

732
00:31:38,196 --> 00:31:39,364
and can even be misunderstood.

733
00:31:40,765 --> 00:31:41,766
Actually, you remind me

734
00:31:42,433 --> 00:31:43,568
of myself when I was young.

735
00:31:49,474 --> 00:31:50,108
Always alone.

736
00:31:50,108 --> 00:31:51,209
Keeping to yourself.

737
00:31:55,647 --> 00:31:56,414
Even in the cafeteria,

738
00:31:57,482 --> 00:31:58,216
you choose a corner

739
00:31:59,584 --> 00:32:00,451
and avoid

740
00:32:00,451 --> 00:32:01,653
unnecessary conversation.

741
00:32:02,287 --> 00:32:03,187
I was the same then.

742
00:32:03,388 --> 00:32:04,355
I cared only about

743
00:32:05,123 --> 00:32:06,124
becoming better.

744
00:32:08,693 --> 00:32:09,794
But really, I just didn't want to admit

745
00:32:09,827 --> 00:32:10,728
there was a void inside me.

746
00:32:14,165 --> 00:32:15,800
A void?

747
00:32:17,535 --> 00:32:18,903
Because of

748
00:32:22,273 --> 00:32:22,840
some childhood experiences,

749
00:32:30,481 --> 00:32:31,316
I shut myself off

750
00:32:31,349 --> 00:32:32,116
for a long time.

751
00:32:33,117 --> 00:32:34,152
It was only a few years ago

752
00:32:37,088 --> 00:32:38,122
that I truly let go of that obsession.

753
00:32:39,757 --> 00:32:42,160
How did you do it?

754
00:32:45,330 --> 00:32:46,597
There wasn't any special method.

755
00:32:52,036 --> 00:32:53,504
But only when you

756
00:32:58,409 --> 00:32:59,077
truly make up your mind

757
00:32:59,077 --> 00:33:00,244
and bravely open yourself

758
00:33:01,813 --> 00:33:02,914
can sunlight come in.

759
00:33:06,351 --> 00:33:07,552
Only then can you truly feel

760
00:33:11,289 --> 00:33:12,890
the warmth others give you.

761
00:33:13,991 --> 00:33:15,193
Thank you, pretty doctor.

762
00:33:33,511 --> 00:33:35,446
Your hair like this

763
00:33:45,156 --> 00:33:45,990
makes you look approachable.

764
00:33:46,691 --> 00:33:47,425
I just saw

765
00:34:03,374 --> 00:34:05,176
Zhang Diao'e in the hallway.

766
00:34:05,209 --> 00:34:06,044
My goodness, she was glowing.

767
00:34:06,511 --> 00:34:08,146
She looked like a different person.

768
00:34:08,246 --> 00:34:09,881
You really haven't

769
00:34:10,214 --> 00:34:11,182
seen much, have you?

770
00:34:11,282 --> 00:34:12,150
Lots of interventional procedures

771
00:34:12,383 --> 00:34:13,317
are like that.

772
00:34:13,317 --> 00:34:13,985
The patient feels different

773
00:34:14,352 --> 00:34:15,186
right there on the table.

774
00:34:15,186 --> 00:34:16,521
The pain is gone. The hypoxia is gone.

775
00:34:16,687 --> 00:34:17,789
Breathing becomes easier.

776
00:34:17,889 --> 00:34:18,723
That's the greatest sense of achievement

777
00:34:18,956 --> 00:34:20,024
we get in the cath lab.

778
00:34:20,124 --> 00:34:21,125
She was simply too good at enduring pain.

779
00:34:22,293 --> 00:34:23,327
Seriously.

780
00:34:23,761 --> 00:34:24,128
If she'd received treatment earlier,

781
00:34:24,362 --> 00:34:25,963
it's hard to imagine

782
00:34:27,231 --> 00:34:28,599
how much suffering she could've avoided.

783
00:34:28,599 --> 00:34:29,600
Then take off that white coat.

784
00:34:39,143 --> 00:34:40,445
And don't let me see you again.

785
00:34:43,014 --> 00:34:44,148
What are you doing?

786
00:34:54,092 --> 00:34:54,592
I got emotional that day.

787
00:34:58,729 --> 00:35:00,364
Looking back, you were right.

788
00:35:01,232 --> 00:35:02,600
I should have

789
00:35:03,835 --> 00:35:04,402
more awareness of protecting patients.

790
00:35:04,402 --> 00:35:05,436
And?

791
00:35:09,640 --> 00:35:10,174
Actually,

792
00:35:13,611 --> 00:35:14,312
most patients

793
00:35:15,246 --> 00:35:16,314
are understanding and grateful.

794
00:35:16,848 --> 00:35:18,749
Even if I only

795
00:35:19,183 --> 00:35:19,884
do a little more

796
00:35:19,884 --> 00:35:20,785
or say one extra

797
00:35:20,885 --> 00:35:21,752
caring word,

798
00:35:21,786 --> 00:35:22,487
it can be a huge comfort to them.

799
00:35:23,921 --> 00:35:24,522
I think

800
00:35:24,555 --> 00:35:25,590
I really can do better.

801
00:35:27,725 --> 00:35:28,292
What does that have to do with me?

802
00:35:29,627 --> 00:35:30,995
I want to keep following

803
00:35:34,065 --> 00:35:34,966
your clinics and surgeries.

804
00:35:35,867 --> 00:35:36,834
Are you ready?

805
00:35:36,934 --> 00:35:37,568
I'm ready.

806
00:35:43,808 --> 00:35:44,809
All right.

807
00:35:50,748 --> 00:35:51,649
Liu Dong.

808
00:35:52,884 --> 00:35:53,251
Let her follow you.

809
00:35:54,318 --> 00:35:54,719
Director.

810
00:35:55,720 --> 00:35:56,354
What?

811
00:35:57,989 --> 00:35:58,456
Director Zhou said

812
00:36:00,958 --> 00:36:01,492
if you refuse,

813
00:36:03,294 --> 00:36:03,995
I should give this to you.

814
00:36:03,995 --> 00:36:04,829
Did you bring your stethoscope?

815
00:36:04,929 --> 00:36:05,730
Yes.

816
00:36:25,650 --> 00:36:26,517
Let's do rounds.

817
00:36:27,652 --> 00:36:28,052
Thank you, Director.

818
00:36:29,120 --> 00:36:29,654
Director, I'll follow you too.

819
00:36:30,688 --> 00:36:31,155
Sit down.

820
00:36:31,556 --> 00:36:32,557
Brother Dong.

821
00:36:32,557 --> 00:36:33,191
Sit.

822
00:36:36,427 --> 00:36:36,894
Be good.

823
00:36:37,161 --> 00:36:37,929
Why?

824
00:36:38,229 --> 00:36:38,629
Why do you change your mind every five minutes?

825
00:36:44,402 --> 00:36:45,236
Don't go.

826
00:36:45,369 --> 00:36:46,671
Zhaobang.

827
00:36:46,671 --> 00:36:47,238
Don't leave. Let's talk this through.

828
00:36:47,471 --> 00:36:47,972
Let's talk.

829
00:36:48,272 --> 00:36:49,907
I don't want another child.

830
00:36:49,974 --> 00:36:51,142
We already have Panpan

831
00:36:54,845 --> 00:36:56,047
and Tingting.

832
00:36:56,747 --> 00:36:58,082
We have two wonderful daughters.

833
00:36:58,115 --> 00:36:58,983
That's enough.

834
00:36:59,083 --> 00:37:00,384
We don't need a son.

835
00:37:00,451 --> 00:37:01,052
Who taught you that?

836
00:37:01,118 --> 00:37:02,587
Who taught you to say that?

837
00:37:03,854 --> 00:37:05,022
I paid so much for your surgery,

838
00:37:05,289 --> 00:37:06,424
and now you say no more children?

839
00:37:07,758 --> 00:37:09,493
You had me treated

840
00:37:09,527 --> 00:37:10,595
just so I could give you a son, right?

841
00:37:13,331 --> 00:37:14,532
Whether I live or die

842
00:37:14,999 --> 00:37:15,833
doesn't matter to you, does it?

843
00:37:15,866 --> 00:37:17,201
I never thought

844
00:37:18,102 --> 00:37:19,237
getting your illness treated

845
00:37:19,270 --> 00:37:20,671
would make you this arrogant.

846
00:37:26,744 --> 00:37:27,945
You've forgotten your place.

847
00:37:30,147 --> 00:37:31,148
If you want a divorce,

848
00:37:31,148 --> 00:37:33,117
just say it.

849
00:37:33,684 --> 00:37:35,286
Fine. Let's divorce.

850
00:37:39,123 --> 00:37:40,424
Every time we argue, you threaten divorce.

851
00:37:41,125 --> 00:37:42,126
Then divorce.

852
00:37:45,663 --> 00:37:46,597
If you want a son,

853
00:37:47,665 --> 00:37:49,533
find someone else to have one.

854
00:37:50,568 --> 00:37:50,968
How dare you hit her?

855
00:37:52,103 --> 00:37:53,304
You...

856
00:37:53,604 --> 00:37:55,172
Try touching her again.

857
00:37:58,075 --> 00:37:59,010
Who are you? Move.

858
00:37:59,010 --> 00:37:59,677
What does this have to do with you?

859
00:37:59,944 --> 00:38:00,845
Doctor.

860
00:38:01,112 --> 00:38:02,346
Move aside.

861
00:38:02,413 --> 00:38:03,147
What are you doing? This is a hospital.

862
00:38:03,147 --> 00:38:03,547
What do you think you're doing?

863
00:38:03,614 --> 00:38:04,282
Touch her again and I'll call security.

864
00:38:04,282 --> 00:38:05,583
He's insane.

865
00:38:05,750 --> 00:38:06,350
Zhang Diao'e,

866
00:38:07,918 --> 00:38:08,986
you dare talk to me like that now?

867
00:38:11,055 --> 00:38:11,889
Fine.

868
00:38:13,591 --> 00:38:14,558
Fine.

869
00:38:17,962 --> 00:38:19,597
What are you staring at?

870
00:38:20,464 --> 00:38:21,165
Are you two okay?

871
00:38:22,233 --> 00:38:23,000
Here, take a tissue.

872
00:38:25,403 --> 00:38:26,237
I've lived half my life like a coward.

873
00:38:29,073 --> 00:38:30,241
He never treated me like a human being.

874
00:38:37,882 --> 00:38:38,582
Then divorce him.

875
00:38:42,386 --> 00:38:45,890
Didn't the village official

876
00:38:48,192 --> 00:38:51,195
just call you?

877
00:38:52,797 --> 00:38:53,831
You'll get land

878
00:38:55,132 --> 00:38:55,833
and compensation too.

879
00:38:55,833 --> 00:38:57,201
You were always entitled

880
00:38:57,968 --> 00:38:58,836
to equal land rights.

881
00:38:59,170 --> 00:39:00,304
You have two hands and two feet.

882
00:39:01,038 --> 00:39:02,373
You can earn money and support yourself.

883
00:39:02,373 --> 00:39:03,407
With Tingting and Panpan,

884
00:39:03,774 --> 00:39:05,376
the three of you

885
00:39:06,811 --> 00:39:08,279
can still live well.

886
00:39:08,512 --> 00:39:09,480
My two daughters

887
00:39:09,480 --> 00:39:10,081
can't grow up to be like me.

888
00:39:10,081 --> 00:39:11,349
Are you ever going to stop?

889
00:39:13,584 --> 00:39:15,152
Where did that fire

890
00:39:16,320 --> 00:39:18,789
you had in school go?

891
00:39:23,994 --> 00:39:25,196
I'm done talking to you.

892
00:39:25,296 --> 00:39:25,830
I'm packing my things.

893
00:39:25,830 --> 00:39:26,997
Then divorce him.

894
00:39:28,032 --> 00:39:28,866
Quan.

895
00:39:29,433 --> 00:39:30,267
Thank you.

896
00:39:59,764 --> 00:40:00,564
You've finally figured it out.

897
00:40:10,975 --> 00:40:11,475
Exactly.

898
00:40:16,247 --> 00:40:17,047
Look at you now.

899
00:40:17,481 --> 00:40:18,282
You're so much more beautiful.

900
00:40:19,316 --> 00:40:20,317
Why stay with him?

901
00:40:20,885 --> 00:40:22,119
From now on,

902
00:40:22,253 --> 00:40:23,087
live for yourself.

903
00:40:23,487 --> 00:40:24,455
You too.

904
00:40:25,990 --> 00:40:26,490
You're transferring

905
00:40:26,724 --> 00:40:27,625
to Rheumatology and Immunology, right?

906
00:40:29,760 --> 00:40:30,694
Yes.

907
00:40:32,563 --> 00:40:34,031
Now that the diagnosis is clear, get treated properly.

908
00:40:34,031 --> 00:40:35,166
I heard those drugs

909
00:40:35,833 --> 00:40:36,133
make people gain weight.

910
00:40:37,268 --> 00:40:39,637
Will that affect

911
00:40:41,205 --> 00:40:42,973
your work?

912
00:40:42,973 --> 00:40:44,208
It's okay.

913
00:40:44,375 --> 00:40:45,276
Dr. Fang said

914
00:40:45,276 --> 00:40:46,243
if it's controlled well now,

915
00:40:46,310 --> 00:40:46,944
that isn't inevitable.

916
00:40:47,077 --> 00:40:48,045
Actually, even if I gain a little weight,

917
00:40:48,045 --> 00:40:49,113
it doesn't matter.

918
00:40:49,213 --> 00:40:49,847
Maybe I can break into

919
00:40:50,548 --> 00:40:51,315
a different niche.

920
00:40:51,415 --> 00:40:52,082
What niche?

921
00:40:52,316 --> 00:40:53,484
I've already thought it through.

922
00:40:53,484 --> 00:40:54,185
Healthy eating

923
00:40:54,518 --> 00:40:55,452
and exercise-based weight loss.

924
00:40:55,753 --> 00:40:56,587
I can still do it.

925
00:40:56,921 --> 00:40:58,189
Look at you.

926
00:40:58,856 --> 00:41:00,090
Don't go back to that company.

927
00:41:00,558 --> 00:41:01,625
And that Brother Xu

928
00:41:01,826 --> 00:41:03,327
is no good either.

929
00:41:03,694 --> 00:41:05,362
I'm definitely not going back.

930
00:41:06,330 --> 00:41:07,431
Next comes

931
00:41:07,565 --> 00:41:09,400
the lawsuit, contract termination,

932
00:41:09,767 --> 00:41:10,868
and getting my money back.

933
00:41:12,269 --> 00:41:13,571
That baboon

934
00:41:14,038 --> 00:41:15,372
can lie to me about love,

935
00:41:15,873 --> 00:41:16,407
but he won't take a cent from me.

936
00:41:16,674 --> 00:41:17,308
Make him pay.

937
00:41:17,374 --> 00:41:18,509
When you do,

938
00:41:19,543 --> 00:41:21,045
tell me.

939
00:41:22,480 --> 00:41:23,247
I'll go with you.

940
00:41:23,614 --> 00:41:24,615
That stupid baboon.

941
00:41:24,648 --> 00:41:25,549
It's over.

942
00:41:25,549 --> 00:41:26,951
I used to think he looked okay.

943
00:41:26,984 --> 00:41:28,152
Now that I've accepted your description,

944
00:41:30,754 --> 00:41:31,789
I can't even

945
00:41:32,323 --> 00:41:34,158
look at his face directly.

946
00:41:34,525 --> 00:41:35,626
All I see in my head

947
00:41:35,693 --> 00:41:36,327
is a baboon.

948
00:41:37,995 --> 00:41:39,196
See? He does look like one.

949
00:41:39,230 --> 00:41:40,598
I told you before and you didn't believe me.

950
00:41:40,598 --> 00:41:41,599
Looks like one, right?

951
00:41:41,599 --> 00:41:44,034
He does.

952
00:41:44,235 --> 00:41:46,503
Look.

953
00:41:47,204 --> 00:41:47,605
By the way,

954
00:41:49,373 --> 00:41:49,773
this

955
00:41:50,174 --> 00:41:50,808
is for you.

956
00:41:57,081 --> 00:41:57,615
What are you giving me?

957
00:41:59,016 --> 00:41:59,516
I don't want it.

958
00:41:59,750 --> 00:42:00,451
Why?

959
00:42:00,985 --> 00:42:01,952
It's too expensive.

960
00:42:04,288 --> 00:42:04,989
Why are you giving me this?

961
00:42:05,289 --> 00:42:05,923
Take it back.

962
00:42:05,923 --> 00:42:06,757
Keep it.

963
00:42:06,824 --> 00:42:07,591
Listen to me.

964
00:42:07,591 --> 00:42:07,992
Showing off your money?

965
00:42:08,025 --> 00:42:08,592
I do have money.

966
00:42:08,692 --> 00:42:09,326
Keep it.

967
00:42:09,326 --> 00:42:10,427
Listen to me.

968
00:42:10,594 --> 00:42:11,228
Showing off your money?

969
00:42:12,396 --> 00:42:13,464
Still, why give me this?

970
00:42:13,631 --> 00:42:14,932
You can use it later

971
00:42:14,965 --> 00:42:16,333
for livestreaming and filming videos.

972
00:42:18,969 --> 00:42:20,404
You give me something like this,

973
00:42:21,205 --> 00:42:22,172
and I'm still supposed to livestream?

974
00:42:22,172 --> 00:42:23,574
How could I show my face?

975
00:42:24,842 --> 00:42:26,310
The police

976
00:42:26,343 --> 00:42:27,144
caught that scammer.

977
00:42:27,711 --> 00:42:29,246
I still don't know

978
00:42:29,280 --> 00:42:30,414
how much of my money I'll recover.

979
00:42:31,348 --> 00:42:32,783
Forget the dream

980
00:42:32,783 --> 00:42:33,717
of getting rich overnight.

981
00:42:33,784 --> 00:42:34,585
But livestreaming

982
00:42:34,652 --> 00:42:35,920
really is something you can do.

983
00:42:37,154 --> 00:42:38,222
You're giving me

984
00:42:38,289 --> 00:42:39,390
such an expensive gift,

985
00:42:39,490 --> 00:42:40,991
and I didn't prepare anything for you.

986
00:42:42,359 --> 00:42:42,826
You did.

987
00:42:44,628 --> 00:42:45,195
What?

988
00:42:46,630 --> 00:42:47,197
Long Quan.

989
00:42:50,367 --> 00:42:51,769
Do a set of Long-style boxing for me.

990
00:42:51,835 --> 00:42:52,403
Stop!

991
00:42:54,672 --> 00:42:55,706
Three against one—

992
00:42:55,839 --> 00:42:56,707
what kind of heroes are you?

993
00:42:57,274 --> 00:42:58,175
Who are you?

994
00:42:58,475 --> 00:42:59,543
Zhang Diao'e.
